     Supreme  Commander:  Forged Alliance delivers an all new strategic
     single-player campaign, an additional playable faction, as well as
     new multiplayer maps to the series that defined scope and scale in
     the  Real-Time Strategy (RTS) genre. Developer by Chris Taylor and
     Gas  Powered  Games,  the  game  is  now available at major retail
     outlets nationwide.

     "Supreme  Commander: Forged Alliance pushes the scope and scale of
     the RTS genre to the next level, offering the largest battlefields
     and  the  biggest  armies  ever seen," said Chris Taylor, CEO, Gas
     Powered Games. "GPG has listened closely to what the fans want and
     we&#039;ve  used  that  feedback  to  make  Supreme  Commander:  Forged
     Alliance the ultimate RTS experience.

     The   game   continues  the  series&#039;  epic  story  in  an  all-new
     single-player  campaign  following  the Infinite War. In addition,
     Supreme   Commander  Forged  Alliance  introduces  the  mysterious
     Seraphim  faction  and includes a myriad of innovative multiplayer
     features.  More  than  100  new  units will give players access to
     cutting-edge  strategic  options, including fully realized navies,
     orbital  weaponry  and advanced counter intelligence technologies.
